title: L3Harris wins $80 million Air Force contract for satcom experiments
summary: The U.S. Air Force Research Laboratory awarded L3Harris Technologies a contract worth $80.8 million to conduct communications experiments using multiple commercial space internet services.

title: NASA to Provide Briefing, Coverage of Spacewalks for Station Upgrades
summary: Two NASA astronauts aboard the International Space Station will conduct a pair of spacewalks Friday, June 9, and Thursday, June 15, to install two new solar arrays.

title: New Mexico Students to Hear from NASA Astronauts Aboard Space Station
summary: Students from southern New Mexico schools will have an opportunity to hear from NASA astronauts aboard the International Space Station.

title: NASA, Rocket Lab Complete Launch of TROPICS CubeSat Constellation
summary: The final pair of NASA’s TROPICS (Time-Resolved Observations of Precipitation structure and storm Intensity with a Constellation of Smallsats) are in orbit after successfully launching at 11:46 p.m. EDT, May 25, (3:46 p.m. NZST Friday, May 26th), completing the constellation.

title: SpaceX investment in Starship approaches $5 billion
summary: SpaceX will have spent $5 billion or more on its Starship vehicle and launch infrastructure by the end of this year, according to court filings and comments by the company’s chief executive.
